snippet.textDisplay: I'm not liking the new iPhone lineup. Before the iPhone X every iPhone was made to be the best which meant the got the best processor, cameras and displays (except for the 5C). Also they were released in pairs (4 & 4s, 8 & 8 plus, etc.) with the only difference between the recent ones being the extra cameras. But then Apple ruined that "linear" release pattern with the iPhone 11 and XR because it decided to cheap out on those with the cameras and displays thereby making it the cost effective models which I think exaggerates the "pro" and "max" models. What I'm getting is now there will be a premium to pay if you want the best iPhone whereas before you got "the whole package" regardless of which iPhone you bought.
snippet.textOriginal: I'm not liking the new iPhone lineup. Before the iPhone X every iPhone was made to be the best which meant the got the best processor, cameras and displays (except for the 5C). But then Apple ruined that "linear" release pattern with the iPhone 11 and XR because it decided to cheap out on those with the cameras and displays thereby making it the cost effective models which I think exaggerates the "pro" and "max" models. What I'm getting is now there will be a premium to pay if you want the best iPhone whereas before you got "the whole package" regardless of which iPhone you bought.
